    <stitle>SPICER 14 INCH (350 MM) SOLO CLUTCH - RESETTING PROCEDURES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl1100403">
        <title>RESETTING PROCEDURES</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>CLUTCH ASSEMBLY OUT OF VEHICLE</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100433">Figure 33</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1100433" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1100433" filename="../figg11/G1100433.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Clutch Assembly Out of Vehicle</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the clutch cover assembly in an arbor press with its pressure plate facing upward.
                    Allow at least one inch clearance between the release bearing and the arbor press table and leave
                    access to the (4) shipping bolts or access holes and wear tab.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Push the retainer downward until the retainers stop contacts the clutch cover. Lock the
                    arbor press in this position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the wear indicating tab clockwise until it is in the new position (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1100434">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1100434" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1100434" filename="../figg11/G1100434.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 34. Wear Indicating Tab</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install and tighten (4) shipping bolts hand tight.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the shipping bolts in a criss-cross pattern until the pressure plate is .500 to
                    .525 inch (12.7 to 13.3 mm) below the cover assembly mounting flange.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the clutch cover assembly from the arbor press and install following
                    <hotlnk document="s11004_HL1100402.xml" xrefid="hl1100402">SINGLE PLATE CLUTCH ASSEMBLY</hotlnk>, or
                    <hotlnk document="s11004_HL1100404.xml" xrefid="hl1100404">TWO PLATE CLUTCH ASSEMBLY</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
